    "title": "Kandinsky Flipping",
    "description": "&quot;As certain as the Correggiosity of Correggio.&quot;\n– Augustine Birrell, 'Obiter Dicta' (?). \n\n&quot;Because any arrangement of squares, circles, and connecting lines has limitations in what it may portray, the organization chart is best regarded as an illustration accompanying a description of the departments, boards, bureaus...&quot;\n– Bureau of Municipal Research (Philadelphia, Pa.) (1932)\n\n&quot;Our experiments [by the artists of 'Cobra'] the aim at letting thought express itself spontaneously without the control which reason represents. By means of this irrational spontaneity we get closer tot the vital source of life. Our goal is to liberate ourselves from the control of reason which has been and still is the thing which the bourgeoisie has idealized to seize control of life.&quot;\n– Asger Jorn (1949) in 'Discours aux pingouins' ('Speech to the Penguins'), in 'Cobra' (1949).\n",
